org.apache.commons.imaging.formats.gif

Enum DisposalMethod

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DisposalMethod>
      • org.apache.commons.imaging.formats.gif.DisposalMethod
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<DisposalMethod>

    public enum DisposalMethod
extends Enum<DisposalMethod>
    Describes the disposal of a GIF frame when rendering the animation. Frames that aren't disposed can show through transparent pixels of coming frames. This allows new layers to contain just the part of the animation that changes.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DO_NOT_DISPOSE
      The next frame should be rendered on top of this frame.
      RESTORE_TO_BACKGROUND
      Dispose the frame and restore the background.
      RESTORE_TO_PREVIOUS
      Dispose the frame and restore the previous undisposed frame.
      TO_BE_DEFINED_1
      Unused method 1.
      TO_BE_DEFINED_2
      Unused method 2.
      TO_BE_DEFINED_3
      Unused method 3.
      TO_BE_DEFINED_4
      Unused method 4.
      UNSPECIFIED
      Typically used for a full-size non-transparent frame that will be replaced by another.
